Scott: You're not spending a lot of time waiting for people to take their turns.

644
00:34:20,650 --> 00:34:22,949
Scott: Your turn doesn't have a whole lot to think about.

645
00:34:22,989 --> 00:34:29,429
Scott: You're thinking more as a collection of turns, but you're still constantly working your way towards that big thing.

646
00:34:29,489 --> 00:34:33,230
Scott: And then the thing about that is everyone's constantly playing.

647
00:34:33,270 --> 00:34:34,310
Scott: You're never out of the game.

648
00:34:34,370 --> 00:34:35,270
Scott: You're not really bored.

649
00:34:35,389 --> 00:34:36,610
Scott: The game keeps you engaged.

650
00:34:36,751 --> 00:34:40,050
Rym: And you don't need to worry about novice players needing to bevagon their ass.

651
00:34:40,310 --> 00:34:50,570
Scott: You don't have to think too hard at any particular juncture, you know, and it keeps the game at a good pace and it makes it a lot of fun for people who aren't super gamers.

652
00:34:51,012 --> 00:34:56,668
Rym: But if you're a hardcore gamer, still buy this game because it's a great game to get people into board gaming.

653
00:34:56,949 --> 00:35:00,069
Rym: And like other games we have that aren't the super best games, it's fun.

654
00:35:00,350 --> 00:35:01,850
Rym: I mean, Carcassonne is solved.

655
00:35:02,010 --> 00:35:05,090
Rym: Settlers is solved, but they can still be fun to play depending on the situation.

656
00:35:05,531 --> 00:35:08,830
Scott: And it can also handle a lot of players, like up to like five players.

657
00:35:08,950 --> 00:35:11,330
Scott: It's not bad for more than some other games.

658
00:35:11,530 --> 00:35:12,610
Rym: It's also a pretty quick play.

659
00:35:12,730 --> 00:35:14,149
Rym: It's something you can just whip out and play now.

660
00:35:15,230 --> 00:35:16,710
Scott: It's also really colorful and happy.

661
00:35:16,990 --> 00:35:17,670
Rym: We didn't own the game.

