00:35:17,710 --> 00:35:22,308
Rym: Our friends James and Lisa had it, so they brought it and we played it with them and we never bought it.

663
00:35:22,570 --> 00:35:24,369
Scott: But we liked it the times we played it.

664
00:35:24,450 --> 00:35:24,541
Scott: Yeah.

665
00:35:24,690 --> 00:35:30,130
Rym: So as a result, I was in the store, a Millennium in Rochester, and I saw Europe Edition.

666
00:35:30,330 --> 00:35:32,290
Rym: I thought, all right, well, I already played the normal one.

667
00:35:32,290 --> 00:35:34,790
Rym: I might as well just buy this edition and own that one instead.

668
00:35:35,050 --> 00:35:35,770
Rym: It can't be that different.

669
00:35:36,251 --> 00:35:39,450
Scott: Well, the Europe version adds two things that are kind of crappy.

670
00:35:40,490 --> 00:35:42,730
Rym: Randomness and more randomness.

671
00:35:43,111 --> 00:35:53,308
Rym: If you, sir, were tired of playing games where skill determines the victor, if you were bad at games and were frustrated at the fact that you lost due to your own lack of ability, have no fear.

672
00:35:53,950 --> 00:35:55,530
Rym: Ticket to Ride Europe is your game.

673
00:35:56,011 --> 00:35:57,250
Scott: So it has these tunnels, right?

674
00:35:57,270 --> 00:35:58,601
Scott: And the way the tunnels work is.

675
00:35:58,621 --> 00:35:59,690
Scott: it's just a normal route.

676
00:35:59,917 --> 00:36:00,128
Scott: Right.

677
00:36:00,651 --> 00:36:03,550
Scott: But if you want to build on the route, you like roll a dice.

678
00:36:03,833 --> 00:36:05,009
Scott: You roll one die, I think.

679
00:36:05,521 --> 00:36:05,690
Scott: Right.

680
00:36:05,792 --> 00:36:06,170
Scott: Is that right?

681
00:36:07,171 --> 00:36:15,070
Rym: No, it's pretty much you play out, like say you play out whatever many cards it is of the right color, and then you draw three more colors.

682
00:36:15,250 --> 00:36:15,442
Rym: Oh, right.

683
00:36:16,230 --> 00:36:21,989
Rym: And if you it's like you have you gamble and you can bet on the odds of finishing the tunnel or not.

684
00:36:22,070 --> 00:36:23,310
Rym: If you finish it, great.

685
00:36:23,390 --> 00:36:25,269
Rym: If you don't, well, you just wasted a turn.

686
00:36:25,703 --> 00:36:25,850
Scott: Yeah.

687
00:36:25,870 --> 00:36:29,710
Scott: It's like basically let's say a tunnel is three trains long.

688
00:36:29,860 --> 00:36:30,010
Scott: Right.

689
00:36:30,071 --> 00:36:32,170
Scott: So I try to build it and I have the three trains.

690
00:36:32,591 --> 00:36:36,070
Scott: Then we do this random thing and it might turn out that I need to.

691
00:36:36,170 --> 00:36:37,149
Rym: I'll read the actual rules.

692
00:36:37,231 --> 00:36:37,403
Scott: OK.

693
00:36:37,690 --> 00:36:42,768
Rym: When attempting to claim a tunnel route, a player first lays down the number of cards required by the route's length.

694
00:36:43,390 --> 00:36:43,812
Rym: Then turn.

695
00:36:43,832 --> 00:36:49,210
Rym: the top three cards from the train deck for each card reveal that matches the color used to claim the route.

696
00:36:49,670 --> 00:36:54,010
Rym: An additional card of the same color must be played to successfully claim the route.

697
00:36:54,631 --> 00:36:58,489
Rym: If a player does not have enough cards, he takes all his cards back and the turn ends.

698
00:36:59,653 --> 00:37:05,269
Scott: Depending on luck, you might lose a turn, but you could sort of mitigate that by having extra cards in your hand.

699
00:37:05,871 --> 00:37:13,328
Scott: But then you might have to spend five cards to build a route that's only three long just to avoid losing a turn.

700
00:37:13,891 --> 00:37:22,588
Scott: So it's basically, you know, you can build this route, but you might get randomly fucked and it doesn't really add a lot to the game, but just sort of makes it annoying if you need one of those routes.

701
00:37:23,831 --> 00:37:30,814
Scott: The other thing the game as the ferries, which basically you need to have wild cards or some number of them to do.

702
00:37:30,854 --> 00:37:37,530
Scott: some of the ferry routes like this is one ferry route that goes from Smyrna to Palermo and it's six spaces long.

703
00:37:38,151 --> 00:37:42,670
Scott: And you could use any four cards you want that are the same color, but even wild cards.

704
00:37:42,750 --> 00:37:46,430
Scott: But you need two wild cards through those last two spots or else you can't do it.

705
00:37:46,611 --> 00:37:48,018
Rym: Now, we haven't played any of the other.

706
00:37:48,099 --> 00:37:50,110
Rym: well, the other expansion is the Marklin.

707
00:37:50,330 --> 00:37:51,310
Scott: It's they're not expansions.

708
00:37:51,510 --> 00:37:52,850
Scott: They're alternate versions of the game.

709
00:37:52,910 --> 00:37:54,049
Scott: You could buy Europe on its own.

710
00:37:54,170 --> 00:37:55,068
Scott: Marklin on its own.

711
00:37:55,555 --> 00:37:56,450
Scott: It's not an expansion.

